accessibility.text: With the fast-spreading coronavirus posing a dire threat to economic growth, the Fed would inject $500 billion in purchases of Treasury securities and at least $200 billion in purchases of mortgage-backed debt “over the coming months.”
The Federal Reserve said it would pump $2,300 billion into the economy ramping up its efforts to help companies and state and local governments suffering financial damage from the coronavirus.
